AT&T Phone for Business features

Enhance your team's productivity with our top features

Address book

Access from anywhere via the online myAT&T portal. Store, edit, and search your entire contacts list. Plus, create group distribution lists to send group voice messages.

All call forwarding

Transfer all your incoming calls to another telephone number.

Call blocking

Block up to 100 numbers from ringing through to your phone.

Call protect

Automatically block calls from likely spammers and scammers.

Call screening

Allows inbound calls dialed from a list of up to 20 designated numbers only to ring through.

Frequently asked questions

Expand all

AT&T Phone for Business is a comprehensive VoIP business phone solution that combines crystal-clear digital calling, over 30 advanced and traditional calling features, and seamless integration with existing analog phone systems.

AT&T Phone for Business is designed to keep phone system costs low with no contract requirements, flexible month-to-month billing, free installation, and compatibility with existing analog phones, making it easy and affordable for small businesses to get started quickly. With bundling options with high-speed fiber internet, it delivers reliable, cost-effective phone service for small business needs.

While the best phone service depends on your individual teams needs and preferences, there are plenty of great reasons to choose AT&T Phone for Business. AT&T Phone for Business includes unlimited calling in the U.S., plus calls to Mexico, Canada, and U.S. territories, more than 30 advanced and traditional calling features like Voice-to-Text transcription.

AT&T Phone for Business includes 30+ advanced and traditional calling features to help you effectively manage inbound and outbound calling. Traditional features include Caller ID, Call Waiting, Call Forwarding, and Three-way Calling. Advanced features include Locate Me, Flexible Caller ID, and Voicemail-to-Text transcription.*

*Caller ID may not always be available for all calls.

AT&T Phone for Business works with most existing analog phones, including analog Key Telephone Systems (KTS). This means that you may not need new phone equipment to use the service.

AT&T Office@Hand is a scalable, easy-to-deploy cloud voice solution that meets the changing needs of mobile, distributed workforces by unifying advanced messaging, video meetings, file sharing, and phone capabilities into a single application. Office@Hand enables you to be more productive virtually anywhere, at any time, and on nearly any device.

We deliver integrated 5G internet backup at no extra cost for our 1 GIG or higher business fiber plans and offer AT&T Managed Internet Backup as an add-on service for our 300Mbps and 500Mbps plans. This protects your business and keeps mission-critical devices up and running in the unlikely event of a power or service outage. 

Coverage not available everywhere. Learn more at att.com/5Gforyou.Ltd availability/areas. Reqs Business Fiber 1 GIG or higher & WNC-CGW452 gateway. Wireless backup does not work in the event of a loss of power. LTE coverage may be used depending on signal availability. Go to att.com/wirelesscoverage for details. Other terms apply.

AT&T Phone for Business is voice service provided over an Internet Protocol (VoIP) digital connection that transmits calls across our highly secure IP network using either AT&T Business Internet or AT&T Business Fiber broadband service.
